&lt;sub&gt;Sometimes people are surprised that code like `x = 1`, where `x` is a parameter name, doesn&#39;t impact on the caller&#39;s argument, but code like `x[0] = 1` does. This happens because *item assignment* and *slice assignment* are ways to **mutate** an existing object, rather than reassign a variable, despite the `=` syntax. See https://stackoverflow.com/questions/575196/ for details.&lt;/sub&gt;

